g.text: If you have the TSDZ2 with the throttle option you will
have the 8-Way cable. If you don't have a throttle, you
are more likely to have the 6-Way cable.
This wire MUST have about 5V (4.7V up to 5.3V)
You will need it only once, so you
can remove the wires after flashing.
BEFORE WIRING THE DC-DC output signal,
configure it to be 5V or it will burn the NRF52840 board!!!
NOTE!!! Wire colouring and pin numbers
may change! Always check with a meter first.
